OL,5,Cworries'
OL,7,FAmong those with no intention of
OL,8,Fintroducing financial advice as a
OL,9,Fbenefit in the near future, the most
OL,10,Fcommon reason given was perceptions
OL,11,Faround the risks of inappropriate
OL,12,Fadvice being given and it reflecting
OL,13,Fbadly on the organisation itself.
OL,15,FSome firms also did not consider
OL,16,Ffinancial advice to be an important
OL,17,Fworkplace benefit.
