OL,3,CSome employers 'cautious of offering
OL,4,Cfinancial advice due to reputation
OL,5,Cworries'
OL,7,FThe research, from Close Brothers'
OL,8,FWorkplace Financial Wellbeing Service,
OL,9,Falso found that, when considering the
OL,10,Fworkplace benefits that would most
OL,11,Fpositively impact their financial
OL,12,Fwellbeing, financial advice came third
OL,13,Fon the list of priorities for
OL,14,Femployees (36%), after pension (52%)
OL,15,Fand private medical cover (38%).
OL,17,FWorkers aged 25 to 34 would be
OL,18,Fparticularly keen on receiving
OL,19,Ffinancial advice, the research
OL,20,Findicated.
