OL,3,CSome employers 'cautious of offering
OL,4,Cfinancial advice due to reputation
OL,5,Cworries'
OL,7,FPensions and retirement advice was
OL,8,Ffound to be the most common type of
OL,9,Fadvice offered.
OL,11,FJeanette Makings, head of workplace
OL,12,Ffinancial wellbeing at Close Brothers,
OL,13,Fsaid: "Despite a clear call for
OL,14,Ffinancial advice in the workplace, it
OL,15,Fis evident employers that do offer it
OL,16,Fare not recognising all employees
OL,17,Fwould benefit from this for all areas
OL,18,Fof personal finance; the need isn't
OL,19,Flimited only to pensions or at
OL,20,Fretirement."
